<p class="BubbleTitleSub">Partner Armies Receive a Taste of US Army Training and Southern Hospitality</p>
<p>By Army Capabilities Integration Center, January 24, 2014</p>
<p>The U.S. Army Training and Doctrine Command (TRADOC) engages 16 partner armies through the Foreign Liaison Officer (FLO) program at Ft. Eustis in Virginia.  FLOs assigned to Army Capabilities Integration Center (ARCIC) observe and interact with capability developers, trainers, and Army leaders who help them gain a better understanding of how our Army is transforming.  This program strengthens our relationships with these countries, improves understanding and future interoperability and is an essential part of TRADOC's contribution to the Army's security cooperation efforts.</p>
