<p class="BubbleTitleSection">More FLO Training: Convoy Ops, DATE, and JRTC Simulations</p>
<p>The second training lane focused on convoy operations.  The training unit was working with Afghan forces, portrayed by local actors, to provide humanitarian relief supplies.  The FLOs visited the evaluated unit's brigade tactical operation center (TOC) and then visited a simulated Afghan brigade TOC complete with Afghan staff role players.</p>
<p>The Commanding General (CG), JRTC hosted the FLOs for lunch at the Special Operations Training Detachment where they discussed many topics including the Decisive Action Training Environment (DATE), special force and conventional force interoperability and regionally aligned forces.</p>
<p>Following lunch with the CG, JRTC the FLOs visited the supporting JRTC simulations center where they observed the training in a virtual environment.  The simulation center discussed how they simulate units and stimulate the exercise through their automation tools.  The formal part of the trip ended with an overview of the JRTC Leader Training Program that prepares commanders and staff for their training and ultimately for their deployment to Afghanistan.</p>
<p>While in Louisiana the FLOs were also exposed to American culture and southern hospitality.  They dined in several local restaurants sampling Cajun cuisine such as crawfish etouffee and blackened gator.</p>
